        <scopecontent>
          <p>Includes portraits, professional photographs, and snapshots of
					 Charles and Maria Jackson; their sons, Francis and Phillip; their grandson,
					 Charles S. Jackson II; and Charles Jackson's brother, Moat. Snapshots include
					 family, friends, automobile trips, and recreational activities, most
					 unidentified as to location, names, and dates. Another group of snapshots
					 documents Francis Jackson's service with the Merchant Marines during World War
					 I. Others who are pictured with family members include Henry Thiele, prominent
					 Portland restaurateur and caterer, and Blanche Sweet, actress.</p>
        </scopecontent>
